Budding act, Ekwe Uchenna professionally known as Fizzyfrosh has opened up on his journey into music and how being versatile shaped his musical career. The digital content creator cum musician disclosed this recently in an exclusive chat with The Nation, he said “I broke into the over-saturated Nigerian music industry using my versatility. One day I’m expressing myself through songwriting and singing, another day through beat making or filmmaking. My entire life revolves around creativity and providing good value”. Speaking on the inspiration behind his debut single dubbed ‘One Night’, he said “My single ‘One night’ was inspired by my friends and UK artistes Chunkz and Yung filly. Ideas for the genre and instrumental came from them, while the lyrics were a freestyle I did the moment my producer played the beat.   619 crew wins Glo Battle of The year finale     Kizz Daniels quits smoking on birthday     Pat Oghre sparks off fresh conversation on girl-child with…   Revealing his plans for the year, the rising star added: “While my song ‘One night’ is doing numbers, I’m currently working on follow-up singles, featuring some of the most notable names in the industry. The plan is to release a few more singles this year, in anticipation for my debut album next year”. Versatile act, Fizzyfrosh is a songwriter, recording artist, music producer, filmmaker and digital content creator who hails from Enugu State, Nigeria. He is a graduate of mass communication and holds a Master’s Degree in Tourism and hospitality management overseas.